swGeneralMgmtMIB.name: swGeneralMgmtMIB
swGeneralMgmtMIB.description: The structure of general management information for enterprise.

Ipv6Address.name: Ipv6Address
Ipv6Address.description: This data type is used to model IPv6 addresses. This is a binary string of 16 octets in network byte-order.

swGenFileSystemMgmtTable.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtTable
swGenFileSystemMgmtTable.description: A list of MIB File System Basic Configuration entries supported by the file update of this agent.

swGenFileSystemMgmtEntry.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtEntry
swGenFileSystemMgmtEntry.description: A File System basic configuration entry that contains objects describing a particular MIB supported by this agent.

swGenFileSystemMgmtIndex.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtIndex
swGenFileSystemMgmtIndex.description: The table index for the file entry. This object describes the file type. runtime-code (1), cfg-file (2), log-file (3)

swGenFileSystemMgmtDscr.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtDscr
swGenFileSystemMgmtDscr.description: The description of the software file purpose in this entry.

swGenFileSystemMgmtServerAddrType.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtServerAddrType
swGenFileSystemMgmtServerAddrType.description: The address type where the file to be downloaded is located, or the address type where the file will be uploaded to.

swGenFileSystemMgmtServerAddr.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtServerAddr
swGenFileSystemMgmtServerAddr.description: The address where the file is to be downloaded from or uploaded to.

swGenFileSystemMgmtInterfaceName.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtInterfaceName
swGenFileSystemMgmtInterfaceName.description: This node is used to specify the interface name when swGenFileSystemMgmtServerAddr is the local link address.

swGenFileSystemMgmtUserName.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtUserName
swGenFileSystemMgmtUserName.description: The user name to access the server.

swGenFileSystemMgmtPassword.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtPassword
swGenFileSystemMgmtPassword.description: The password to access the server.

swGenFileSystemMgmtServerFileName.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtServerFileName
swGenFileSystemMgmtServerFileName.description: The name of the file to be downloaded from or uploaded to the server.

swGenFileSystemMgmtDeviceFileName.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtDeviceFileName
swGenFileSystemMgmtDeviceFileName.description: The name of the file to be downloaded to the device, or uploaded from the device. When downloading or uploading, the swGenFileSystemMgmtServerFileName object must also be set.

swGenFileSystemMgmtLoadType.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtLoadType
swGenFileSystemMgmtLoadType.description: This object allows the user to select a download or upload function for the file. Note: For systems that do not support changes to this object, setting a value for this object will cause the system to return a bad-value error message.

swGenFileSystemMgmtCtrl.name: swGenFileSystemMgmtCtrl
swGenFileSystemMgmtCtrl.description: This object allows the user to download runtime software. The settings will take effect when the system restarts. See Note (1) below Note 1: For systems which do not support value changes to this object, setting these values will cause the system to return a bad-value error message. start (3) - activate firmware.

swGenFileSystemBootupFileMgmtTable.name: swGenFileSystemBootupFileMgmtTable
swGenFileSystemBootupFileMgmtTable.description: This table indicates the information about the bootup files.

swGenFileSystemBootupFileMgmtEntry.name: swGenFileSystemBootupFileMgmtEntry
swGenFileSystemBootupFileMgmtEntry.description: A list of information about the bootup files for each unit of the switch stack.

swGenMgmtUnitID.name: swGenMgmtUnitID
swGenMgmtUnitID.description: The object indicates the unit ID.

swGenFileSystemBootImage.name: swGenFileSystemBootImage
swGenFileSystemBootImage.description: When displayed, it shows the current bootup image file name. When set, the bootup image file with the set name will be set as the bootup image.

swGenFileSystemBootConfig.name: swGenFileSystemBootConfig
swGenFileSystemBootConfig.description: When displayed, it shows the current bootup configuration file name. When set, the configuration file with the set name will be set as the bootup configuration.

swGenFileSystemActiveConfigIncrement.name: swGenFileSystemActiveConfigIncrement
swGenFileSystemActiveConfigIncrement.description: If increment is specified, then the existing configuration will not be cleared before applying of the new configuration. If it is not specified, then the existing configuration will be cleared before applying of the new configuration. True : keep valid False : erase.

swGenFileSystemActiveConfig.name: swGenFileSystemActiveConfig
swGenFileSystemActiveConfig.description: When displayed, it shows NULL. When set, the configuration file with the set name will be active at once, but the set name will not be set as the bootup configuration.

swGenExpansionModuleMgmtTable.name: swGenExpansionModuleMgmtTable
swGenExpansionModuleMgmtTable.description: This table indicates the information about the Boot-up Expansion Module and current Expansion Module.

swGenExpansionModuleMgmtEntry.name: swGenExpansionModuleMgmtEntry
swGenExpansionModuleMgmtEntry.description: A list of information about the bootup files for each unit of the switch stack.

swGenExpansionModuleMgmtSlotID.name: swGenExpansionModuleMgmtSlotID
swGenExpansionModuleMgmtSlotID.description: The object indicates the expansion module slot ID.

swGenExpansionModuleMgmtBootup.name: swGenExpansionModuleMgmtBootup
swGenExpansionModuleMgmtBootup.description: It displays the expansion module name which the device boot up with. if no expansion module exist when boot up, it displays 'none'.

swGenExpansionModuleMgmtCurrent.name: swGenExpansionModuleMgmtCurrent
swGenExpansionModuleMgmtCurrent.description: It displays the current exsit expansion module name. if no expansion module exist, it displays 'none'.

swGenExpansionModuleBootupPortModeInfo.name: swGenExpansionModuleBootupPortModeInfo
swGenExpansionModuleBootupPortModeInfo.description: This object is a set of port mode for boot up DXS-3600-EM-4QXS module indications. Every bytes are presented to a port of the DXS-3600-EM-4QXS, if the module is not DXS-3600-EM-4QXS, cannot get any value. Port mode: 01 = 4*10G. 02 = 40G.

swGenExpansionModuleCurrentPortModeMGT.name: swGenExpansionModuleCurrentPortModeMGT
swGenExpansionModuleCurrentPortModeMGT.description: This object is a set of port mode for current insert DXS-3600-EM-4QXS module indications. Every bytes are presented to a port of the DXS-3600-EM-4QXS, it will not write to Equipped module until excute save configuration. Port mode: 01 = 4*10G. 02 = 40G.

swGenExpansionModuleEquippedModulePortMo.name: swGenExpansionModuleEquippedModulePortMode
swGenExpansionModuleEquippedModulePortMo.description: This object is a set of port mode for current insert DXS-3600-EM-4QXS module indications. Every bytes are presented to a port of the DXS-3600-EM-4QXS, if the module boot up with and current insert is not DXS-3600-EM-4QXS, cannot set the port mode management value to Equipped module. Port mode: 01 = 4*10G. 02 = 40G.

swGenMgmtSaveConfigFileName.name: swGenMgmtSaveConfigFileName
swGenMgmtSaveConfigFileName.description: The name of the configuration file that will be saved to the device. When swGenMgmtSave is set to configuration(2): If the swGenMgmtSaveConfigFileName is no NULL, the configuration file will be saved to the set file name. If NULL, the configuration file will be saved to the start-up configuration file.

swGenMgmtSave.name: swGenMgmtSave
swGenMgmtSave.description: This indicates the method of saving information to the NV-RAM of the device. other(1) - No action. configuration(2) - Save configuration. log(3) - Save log. all(4) - Save both ( active configuration and log).
